articles.title: How will Iran respond to killing of Soleimani?
articles.description: Ayman Mohyeldin and Yasmin Vossoughian are joined by MSNBC analyst Juan Zarate and the Daily Beast’s Christopher Dickey to discuss how Iran may retaliate after a U.S. airstrike killed Gen. Qassem Soleimani.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Tensions rise in Middle East after U.S. kills top Iran general
articles.description: Iran is vowing “harsh retaliation” against the U.S. after an airstrike in Baghdad killed Gen. Qassem Soleimani, a top commander of Iran’s Quds Force. NBC’s Richard Engel joins Ayman Mohyeldin and Yasmin Vossoughian to discuss the fallout and why it is difficu…

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: After Trump’s strike on Iran, bracing for retaliation
articles.description: Iran vowed to seek revenge on the United States on Friday after an American airstrike killed one of the country's most powerful military and political figures, Qassem Soleimani. What’s next and will the escalation in conflict lead to a war?
